Networking Concepts

1. Internet History & Organizations
1.1 ARPA (Advanced Research Projects Agency) → DARPA → ARPANET: First packet-switching network, foundation of today’s Internet (1960s).
1.2 WWW (World Wide Web): Service on top of the Internet (Email, FTP).
1.3 Internet Society (ISOC)
1.4 ISP (Internet Service Providers)

2. Networking Infrastructure & Terms
2.1 Networking Terms: LAN, WAN, MAN, PAN, VPN, GAN
2.2 Encryption / Decryption: Symmetric, Asymmetric, Hash Verification, Brute-Force (Cryptanalysis)
2.3 Networking Topologies: Bus, Star, Ring, Mesh, Tree, Hybrid

3. Protocols & Standards
3.1 IP, TCP, UDP
3.2 HTTP / HTTPS
3.3 FTP / SFTP
3.4 SMTP, IMAP, POP3
3.5 DNS, DHCP, NAT

